claim.claim-text:
11. The rubber-reinforcing fiber according to any one of claims 1 to 10, wherein the organic fiber comprises a polyester monofilament cord made of poly(ethylene terephthalate) or mainly made of poly(ethylene terephthalate), and satisfies all the following requirements: 
(a) intrinsic viscosity: 0.85 dl/g or higher; 
(b) birefringence: 0.17 or higher; 
(c) crystal orientation: 0.88 or higher; 
(d) density: 1.32 g/cm3 or higher; 
(e) fineness: 1000 to 9000 dtex; 
(f) tenacity: 5.2 gf/dtex or higher; and 
(g) initial modulus: 50 gf/dtex or higher.
